data.title: Burkina Faso Age dependency ratio - data, chart
data.meta_description: Burkina Faso: Dependent people as percent of the working age population: The latest value from 2022 is 86.07 percent, a decline from 87.4 percent in 2021. In comparison, the world average is 58.67 percent, based on data from 196 countries. Historically, the average for Burkina Faso from 1960 to 2022 is 91.51 percent. The minimum value, 74.1 percent, was reached in 1960 while the maximum of 102.29 percent was recorded in 1993.
